              <span id="reviewTextContainer596926501" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10391782997058965201">If you are looking something to make you feel good, to take to in distant land or a gripping murder mystery or a book on long journey- I wouldn&apos;t recommend it.<br/><br/>BUT if you want to see how you work in a situation, how your friends and people around you are, how our big yet small country is and when it comes to values, humility and culture- This it is the book for you. 51 stories, small yet impactful incidents in the life of Mrs. Murthy, will bring joy and sometimes tears but overwhelming you each t</span>
  <span id="freeText10391782997058965201" style="display:none">If you are looking something to make you feel good, to take to in distant land or a gripping murder mystery or a book on long journey- I wouldn't recommend it.<br /><br />BUT if you want to see how you work in a situation, how your friends and people around you are, how our big yet small country is and when it comes to values, humility and culture- This it is the book for you. 51 stories, small yet impactful incidents in the life of Mrs. Murthy, will bring joy and sometimes tears but overwhelming you each time for the grace and disgrace of so called society. <br /><br />After every story, you can't move to another one with another flip of page because at the end it makes you think and think hard about you and world around you. And, in someway making you better person. <br /><br />I thank her for that. For her honest and grounded writing which can change the heart of people.</span>
